# Beartropy Permissions - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This project uses **Beartropy Permissions**, a Livewire admin UI for spatie/laravel-permission.

## Main Component
```blade
@livewire('beartropy-permissions::permissions-manager')
```

## Livewire Components
```
beartropy-permissions::permissions-manager    # Full tabbed UI
beartropy-permissions::roles-table            # Roles table
beartropy-permissions::permissions-table      # Permissions table
beartropy-permissions::users-table            # Users table
beartropy-permissions::role-modal             # Create/edit role
beartropy-permissions::permission-modal       # Create/edit permission
beartropy-permissions::role-permissions-modal # Assign permissions to role
beartropy-permissions::user-assignments-modal # Assign roles/permissions to user
```

## Configuration
```php
// config/beartropy-permissions.php
'prefix' => 'permissions',
'middleware' => ['web', 'auth', 'can:manage-permissions'],
'gate' => 'manage-permissions',
'user_model' => App\Models\User::class,
'group_permissions' => true,
'permission_group_separator' => '.',
```

## Best Practices
- Define the `manage-permissions` gate before using the package
- Use dot notation for permissions: `users.create`, `users.edit`, `posts.publish`
- The User model must use `Spatie\Permission\Traits\HasRoles`
- All CRUD operations check the configured gate automatically
